---
import LegalLayout from '~/layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { BRAND_NAME, CONTACT_EMAIL } from '~/data/site';
---

<LegalLayout routeKey="accessibility">
  <p>
    {BRAND_NAME} targets <strong>WCAG 2.2 Level AA</strong> on every public
    route. We test with axe-core, the latest VoiceOver, NVDA and JAWS, and a
    keyboard-only operator on every release.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Our commitments</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Every interactive element is reachable by Tab and operable by Enter / Space.</li>
    <li>A skip-to-content link appears as the first focusable element.</li>
    <li>Focus indicators are always visible and meet 3:1 contrast against the surrounding background.</li>
    <li>All non-decorative images carry meaningful alt text.</li>
    <li>Colour contrast ratios are at least 4.5:1 for body copy and 3:1 for large text.</li>
    <li>Animation respects <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>; large transforms stop on request.</li>
    <li>Forms have visible labels, error states and helpful descriptions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Known issues</h2>
  <p>
    We aim for zero known accessibility issues. If you find one, please report it -
    we will fix it on the next deploy and credit you in the changelog.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Reporting a barrier</h2>
  <p>
    Email <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a> with the URL,
    the device and assistive technology you were using, and a description of the
    barrier. We respond within two business days.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Standards</h2>
  <p>
    This statement is based on the W3C Web Content Accessibility Guidelines
    2.2. {BRAND_NAME} is also designed to comply with the EN 301 549 European
    accessibility standard.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Statement preparation</h2>
  <p>
    This statement was last reviewed by an internal accessibility auditor on
    the date shown above and tested against axe-core 4.10.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
